<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-04-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="347" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-04-15"><hi rend="italic">April 15,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(The minister is informed that the department approves the proposed
                            amendments of the Shanghai mixed court rules sent him by Consul-General
                            Goodnow, and he is instructed to urge the adoption of them.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>